  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Value metrics help a team confirm they are delivering the value their stakeholders need and expect. Because value is&#xD;
    perceived from the stakeholder's perspective, a combination of objective and subjective measurements should be&#xD;
    considered. Understanding a project's Value status is critical for planning, executing, and evaluating the project.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Value status requires knowing:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        the stakeholders' level of satisfaction&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        the number of enhancements requested by stakeholders&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Value Metrics&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following metrics can help a team determine their Value status:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Core Metrics&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial&quot;>&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.mgmt.common.extend_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/customer_satisfaction_721A1F11.html&quot; guid=&quot;_IYKpQLQuEd6HgZ8EwRW1Og&quot;>Customer Satisfaction&lt;/a> ratings provide a subjective measurement of client&#xD;
        satisfaction and perception of value. Ratings are obtained through stakeholder surveys.&lt;/span>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.mgmt.common.extend_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/enhancement_request_trend_6560BA36.html&quot; guid=&quot;_vyouZpbmEd27uMM_wDtgBA&quot;>Enhancement Request Trend&lt;/a> shows the trend of enhancement requests received,&#xD;
        approved, and closed during the project lifecycle. A high number of enhancement requests can indicate that the&#xD;
        system is not functioning as stakeholders expected.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Supplementary Metrics&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.mgmt.common.extend_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/iteration_velocity_807B594F.html&quot; guid=&quot;_sg-3YOorEdyXraj7Kl_Siw&quot;>Iteration Velocity&lt;/a> tracks the rate at which a team delivers working software&#xD;
        (that is valuable to stakeholders) in each iteration.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Stakeholder Feedback helps the team monitor the number or frequency of stakeholders providing feedback (for&#xD;
        example, the number of stakeholders who attend the iteration results meeting).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.tech.common.extend_supp_metrics-ibm/guidances/supportingmaterials/enhancement_request_aging_4E07F568.html&quot; guid=&quot;_IiPGMLUpEd6FZfmcIw9rww&quot;>Age of Enhancement Requests&lt;/a> tracks the length of time stakeholder enhancement&#xD;
        requests remain open. Unaddressed requests can impact the stakeholders' perception of value.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Reporting Project Value Status in a Dashboard&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following dashboard example represents one way to calculate and report Value status. Teams can substitute metrics&#xD;
    that are already in place and used successfully in their organization for a custom Value report.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Produce this dashboard by harvesting metrics data and populating a spreadsheet. Generate the dashboard report using&#xD;
    charting capabilities of the spreadsheet tool. Or, the team can use the spreadsheet as a data source and create a&#xD;
    custom report in IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg;. Our intent is to provide these types of dashboards over time as out of the&#xD;
    box reports in IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg;.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    To assess a project's Value status with this dashboard, the following inputs are needed (provided by the Value core&#xD;
    metrics and team-specific variables):&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;table style=&quot;WIDTH: 937px; HEIGHT: 115px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; width=&quot;937&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>Value&lt;/font>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>&lt;strong>Description&lt;/strong>&lt;/font>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>&lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>AVERAGE_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING&lt;/span>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #3366ff; FONT-FAMILY: Arial&quot;>&lt;span                     style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>&lt;span                      style=&quot;COLOR: #000000&quot;>Average score of all customer satisfaction ratings in the last&#xD;
                    iteration&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>&lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>MIN_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING&lt;/span>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>The&#xD;
                minimum customer satisfaction score acceptable for the project&lt;/span>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>&lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>ENHANCEMENT_REQUESTS&lt;/span>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    &lt;span                     style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Actual&#xD;
                    number of enhancement requests submitted by stakeholders&lt;/span>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>&lt;strong>ASSUMED_MAX_ENHANCEMENT_REQ&lt;/strong>&lt;/span>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;span                 style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-language: KO; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-font-family: Batang; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>Projected&#xD;
                number of enhancement requests. This number should be adjusted by phase.&lt;/span>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;strong>Value dashboard status is calculated as follows:&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;table style=&quot;WIDTH: 941px; HEIGHT: 443px&quot; width=&quot;941&quot; border=&quot;4&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; width=&quot;72&quot; bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>Status&lt;/font>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/th>&#xD;
            &lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; width=&quot;377&quot; bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>Definition&lt;/font>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/th>&#xD;
            &lt;th scope=&quot;col&quot; width=&quot;461&quot; bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;>Actions to Take&lt;/font>&#xD;
            &lt;/th>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#ff0000&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>RED&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    If any of the following are true:&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        AVERAGE_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING &amp;lt; MIN_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        ENHANCEMENT_REQUESTS &amp;gt; ASSUMED_MAX_ENHANCEMENT_REQ (for this phase)&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Status is red if your average customer satisfaction rating is lower than the minimally acceptable&#xD;
                    rating defined by the team. Or, the number of enhancement requests submitted by stakeholders is greater&#xD;
                    than expected.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    The following actions can be taken to increase the stakeholder's perception of value:&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Collaborate with the stakeholders to identify their highest priority functionality and prioritize&#xD;
                        it ahead of other work items. Make sure that prioritization is based on business value to the&#xD;
                        stakeholders.&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Review past customer surveys to make sure that the team has followed up on all stakeholder issues.&#xD;
                        Take action to resolve outstanding issues and concerns.&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        Clarify requirements to make sure there is a shared understanding of expected functionality.&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#33CC66&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>GREEN&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    If all of the following are true:&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        AVERAGE_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING &amp;gt; MIN_CUSTOMER_SAT_RATING.&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                        ENHANCEMENT_REQUESTS &amp;lt; = ASSUMED_MAX_ENHANCEMENT_REQ (for this phase).&#xD;
                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Status is green if your average customer satisfaction rating is equal to or greater than the minimally&#xD;
                    acceptable rating defined by the team, and the number of enhancement requests submitted by stakeholders&#xD;
                    is less than or equal to the number expected.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                Good job! The project appears to be delivering the value that stakeholders expect. Continue to monitor&#xD;
                Value status at the end of each iteration for any change.&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td bgcolor=&quot;#ffff00&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>YELLOW&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/div>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                Value status is Red, and we have a plan to address the issue(s)&lt;br />&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Analyze Value metrics to determine the underlying causes for red status. Collaborate with stakeholders&#xD;
                    to determine what actions to take and create a plan to address the issues. Follow the plan and monitor&#xD;
                    progress in each iteration until status is green.&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
                &lt;p>&#xD;
                    Consult the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../publish.bus.practices_for_perf_measurement.base-ibm/customcategories/increase_value_8277C17D.html&quot; guid=&quot;_sD4pkLbFEd6_i8GY7ieNyA&quot;>Value Traceability Tree for Value&lt;/a> help identify strategies and&#xD;
                    solutions to increase value.&lt;br />&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Considerations&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Value is delivered when the software put in production returns on the customer's investment over time in terms of&#xD;
    revenue increase, cost savings, customer relations, service improvement, or reputation.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Value can be calculated:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        At the close of each iteration when working software is delivered (potential value delivered by the project team).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        At the time of product release.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Post release, to confirm the customer is realizing expected value.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The faster high quality software can be rolled out, the quicker its value can be realized. Business involvement is&#xD;
    essential to making sure that the highest value features are prioritized accordingly. The development team cannot do&#xD;
    this in isolation. The product owner's primary responsibility is to make prioritization decisions based on the business&#xD;
    value of each feature (drawing on the project's business objectives to determine the appropriate priority to assign).&#xD;
    As features are delivered throughout the project, return on investment can be projected based on business value&#xD;
    delivered by the team.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Customer Satisfaction Surveys&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    The most effective way to confirm that stakeholders are satisfied and are receiving the value they expect is to ask&#xD;
    them. A Customer Satisfaction Survey contains qualitative questions answered subjectively by the stakeholders.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Typical survey items include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How satisfied are you with the system's capabilities? Does it meet your needs in terms of functionality?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Have your expectations of value been met? Which expectations of value were met or exceeded? Which expectations were&#xD;
        not met?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Are you using the product as intended? Why or why not?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        How would you rate the overall relationship with the team?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Stakeholders should provide answers in a combination of textual and numeric responses. Answers provided using a defined&#xD;
    scale allow for quantifiable results, while prose answers can help with detailed root cause analysis of the numerical&#xD;
    results.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Surveys should be delivered regularly throughout the lifecycle and post-delivery to monitor stakeholder satisfaction&#xD;
    levels. Frequency will vary by project. Some projects benefit from conducting a survey following each iteration demo.&#xD;
    Others find that every six weeks to three months is sufficient. As with all types of stakeholder feedback, it is best&#xD;
    to learn of a potential problem early, than to wait so long that a particular stakeholder concern becomes a real&#xD;
    problem.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    Following up on survey ratings is critical. Collaborate with stakeholders to address issues and concerns.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Enhancement Requests&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    The number of Enhancement Requests submitted can indicate whether the delivered software is meeting the stakeholders'&#xD;
    needs and value expectations. Analyze each incoming request to determine the reason behind the proposed change.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    If the requested change is a completely new requirement (unknown to the team and the stakeholders at the time of&#xD;
    initial planning) then it is unlikely to indicate a problem with the customer's perception of value. However, if the&#xD;
    change involves functionality or usability the customer expected and did not receive, the customer's satisfaction level&#xD;
    and perception of value is likely impacted. These Enhancement Requests should be typed accordingly to monitor the trend&#xD;
    of occurrence over time.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    A high number of Enhancement Requests is to be expected in early project iterations. An ongoing trend of increasing&#xD;
    Enhancement Requests could indicate that the software delivered is not meeting the customer's value expectations. When&#xD;
    this trend occurs, the team should evaluate its requirements gathering process, and confirm that they have regular and&#xD;
    frequent interaction with their stakeholders.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfalls and Countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Customer Satisfaction Surveys&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Customer Satisfaction Surveys should be part of the ongoing process of obtaining frequent and regular stakeholder&#xD;
    feedback. However, too many surveys or overly complex questions can negatively impact results. Ensure that completing a&#xD;
    survey is simple and relatively quick for your stakeholders. Automated, web-based surveys can reduce the overhead in&#xD;
    survey participation and analysis. Confirm that the purpose of the survey is clear to your stakeholders to maximize&#xD;
    participation.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Enhancement Request Trends&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    A large number of Enhancement Requests can indicate a problem with customer satisfaction. However, this trend is also&#xD;
    seen when delivered software is, in fact, very valuable to the customer. When software is widely used, more Enhancement&#xD;
    Requests are an inevitable result.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    In some cases, development teams are penalized for defects and rewarded for implementing enhancements (reflected in&#xD;
    either performance reviews or project budget). This could influence the process of typing incoming Enhancement&#xD;
    Requests. In order for this metric to be useful in assessing Business Value, it is essential that the team work&#xD;
    collaboratively with the stakeholders to accurately reflect the type of each incoming request.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
